-- Pitney Bowes swings to quarterly profit
-- 
-- Mon Jul 30, 2007 4:26pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/07/30/us-pitneybowes-results-idUSWEN985920070730

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Pitney Bowes Inc ( PBI.N ), the largest U.S. supplier of postage meters and mailing machines, on Monday posted a quarterly profit, driven by mail-related services 

 The company, whose mailing meters are a fixture in corporate offices, said its second quarter net income was $152.2 million, or 68 cents a share, compared with a net loss of $356.1 million, or $1.59 per share a year earlier. The year ago figures included costs related to restructuring. Revenue increased 11 percent to $1.5 billion (Reporting by  Paul Thomasch  and  Franklin Paul )